        <div class="snippet-answer">
          <p>A <strong>nano-influencer</strong> is a social media creator with 1,000 to 10,000 followers whose small, highly engaged audience trusts their recommendations more than those from larger accounts. They are not pursuing fame — they are everyday people with genuine expertise in specific niches, whose followers are real community members, not passive scrollers. They average <strong>5-8% engagement rates, 3-5x higher than mega-influencers</strong>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="term-meta-strip">
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Follower range</div>
            <div class="tms-value">1,000 – 10,000</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Category</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Social Media</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Avg engagement rate</div>
            <div class="tms-value">5-8% (vs 1-2% mega)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Cost per post</div>
            <div class="tms-value">$50-$250 or free product</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="lede-p">Trust is marketing's most valuable currency, and nano-influencers have it in abundance. Their followers are real friends, family, and community members — not passive audience members who followed a celebrity. When a nano-influencer recommends something, it reads like a friend's recommendation, not an advertisement.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is a nano-influencer?</h2>
        <p>The influencer marketing spectrum by follower count:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Nano-influencer:</strong> 1,000 – 10,000 followers</li>
          <li><strong>Micro-influencer:</strong> 10,000 – 100,000 followers</li>
          <li><strong>Macro-influencer:</strong> 100,000 – 1 million followers</li>
          <li><strong>Mega-influencer / Celebrity:</strong> 1 million+ followers</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Nano-influencers sit at the bottom of this hierarchy by size, but at the top by engagement rate and trust density. Their content feels like a conversation rather than a broadcast because it often is — their followers are people who actually know them, worked with them, or found them through a shared niche community.</p>
        <p>According to Influencer Marketing Hub, nano-influencers average 5-8% engagement rates. Mega-influencers average 1-2%. On a per-impression basis, the engagement gap is significant — and engagement is what drives clicks, conversions, and brand memory.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">The trust arithmetic</div>
          <p>A nano-influencer with 5,000 followers and a 7% engagement rate generates 350 engaged interactions per post. A mega-influencer with 2 million followers and a 1% engagement rate generates 20,000 — but at roughly 100x the cost. When you activate 50 nano-influencers, you get 17,500 engaged interactions at likely a fraction of the mega-influencer's fee.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="why-it-matters">Why nano-influencers matter for brands</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Highest engagement rates.</strong> 5-8% average engagement vs 1-2% for mega-influencers. More engagement per impression means more clicks, saves, shares, and purchase intent signals generated per dollar spent.</li>
          <li><strong>Lowest costs.</strong> $50-$250 per post, or free product. The budget to engage one macro-influencer can fund 20-50 nano-influencer partnerships with combined reach that may exceed the macro-influencer while producing better engagement metrics.</li>
          <li><strong>Authentic user-generated content.</strong> Posts from nano-influencers look like organic recommendations because they often are. This content performs better in paid boosting because it bypasses "ad blindness" — audiences don't immediately recognise it as sponsored.</li>
          <li><strong>Hyper-local reach.</strong> Nano-influencers in your city or neighbourhood can drive foot traffic and local brand awareness that national campaigns miss entirely. A local food blogger with 3,000 followers can fill your weekend service.</li>
          <li><strong>Scale through volume.</strong> One macro-influencer is a single point of failure. Fifty nano-influencers create a diversified campaign where the overall performance smooths out variance across individual posts.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="how-it-works">How to run a nano-influencer programme</h2>
        <p>Three components make nano-influencer campaigns work at scale:</p>

        <h3>Finding nano-influencers</h3>
        <p>The best source is already in your CRM: customers, email subscribers, and social followers. Many nano-influencers are already fans of your product — they just haven't been activated yet. Check who tags your brand, reviews your products, or posts in communities related to your niche.</p>
        <p>For systematic discovery: search hashtags in your niche on Instagram and TikTok, filter for accounts with 1,000-10,000 followers, and check engagement rate manually or via tool. Grin, Aspire, and Upfluence allow filtering by follower count and engagement rate at scale.</p>

        <h3>Partnership structure</h3>
        <p>Keep arrangements simple for nano-influencers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Product only:</strong> Send free product with a brief. Most nano-influencers who genuinely like your product will post without payment.</li>
          <li><strong>Product + small fee:</strong> $50-$150 plus product builds goodwill and increases post commitment and quality.</li>
          <li><strong>Affiliate / unique discount code:</strong> Aligns incentives — they earn when their followers buy. Trackable and scalable.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Scale through volume</h3>
        <p>One nano-influencer will not move campaign metrics. The strategy is to activate many simultaneously. Build a roster of 30-100 nano-influencers in your niche, send product and briefs in waves, and track performance per creator to identify your top performers for repeat engagement.</p>

